Configuring SSH keys for Github



1 - Generate an ssh key:
$ ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C your@email.com

2 - Add the PRIVATE key to ssh-agent:
$ ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa

3 - Copy the PUBLIC key to clipboard:
$ cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub

4 - Add the PUBLIC key to Github config at https://github.com/settings/keys
(give the public key a good name like "personal laptop" for example)
(the type of the key must be "authentication key", and not "signing key")




To automatically use the ssh key when pushing / pulling a repo:
$ git remote remove origin
$ git remote add origin git@github.com:user_name/repo_name.git
$ git push --set-upstream origin branch_name
